</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AJR1:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AJR1"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AJR &#xA;              1-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Joint Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Jackson<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>December 02, 2024</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to the Sudan conflict. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AJR 1, as introduced, Jackson.
                          Sudan conflict.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would declare the conflict in Sudan an international crisis and would call upon the Trump Administration and the international community to take greater action and bring aid to the people of Sudan.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_81A495BF-8FCF-4ABB-B0F3-AEE1E405B34E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, War erupted in April 2023 due to a power struggle between Sudan’s army and the paramilitary Rapid Support Forces (RSF), halting the country’s planned transition to civilian rule; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C2717236-F70B-4982-87B5-70F12EC3DEBF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The conflict has led to thousands of civilian deaths, with widespread reports of atrocities, including mass rapes and ethnically driven violence; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8EEA9843-D8A3-468F-97C7-9B5B2B3F73FD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, More than 25,000,000 people, one-half of Sudan’s population, need humanitarian aid, with famine already reported in displacement camps; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_493BBC42-2A8D-4298-8CCE-7DE84D9C98FB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, More than 14,000,000 people have been forced to flee their homes, creating the world’s largest displacement crisis, with nearly 3,000,000 seeking refuge in neighboring countries; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_675457E9-DD61-48AF-A7C3-E5F177F2B123"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The RSF has been implicated in systematic ethnic violence, including the recent massacre in El Gezira, where at least 124 civilians were killed; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3D86918F-3D8C-4FA7-BDC0-9C3DE1B7BA1A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The RSF has destroyed towns and villages, looting properties and vandalizing infrastructure in regions like east-central Gezira; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6773312A-F1FE-4DD0-A2C7-E708B606203A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The RSF confiscated communication tools like Starlink devices, limiting civilians’ ability to report abuses and communicate with the outside world; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_9DA31E73-2625-459B-B61D-B161606E6689"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Approximately 25,600,000 people are projected to experience acute hunger, with 775,000 facing faminelike conditions in 2024; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_2AD1EC24-0CCB-4D20-BE70-F6768ECE4964"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Amid global attention on the Middle East, United Nations officials stress that the “forgotten crisis” in Sudan urgently needs increased international support; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_92AB2357-6134-4C3F-9AF5-1661EC2922B6"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Sudan’s government warns that the Adre border crossing from Chad is being used for arms smuggling, worsening the conflict; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E7ED9AD0-AA6B-4542-B980-7D0401BEA880"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Both the Sudanese military and RSF have intensified offensives, with no clear path to ceasefire or resolution; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3F3290DB-2967-4FFC-95C9-0392DBB1CD22"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, United Nations Secretary-General António Guterres said the situation is too volatile for a United Nations force deployment; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3B5C4A7D-4C2B-4130-8D75-342FD2B9533F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The conflict threatens to destabilize Africa’s Sahel and East Africa regions, creating broader international security concerns; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_BCD246D3-AA56-4F6F-850C-05B3919F7A86"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly and the Senate of the State of California, jointly, That the Legislature of the State of California declares the conflict in Sudan to be an international crisis; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_F59407A7-1F7F-4867-981B-577B2B62B32D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature of the State of California calls upon the Trump Administration and the international community to take greater action and bring aid to the people of Sudan; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_6BF2C3F6-5E0F-4F9B-B70D-666DFAC1A2D1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the President and Vice President of the United States, to the Secretary of State, to the Secretary of the Treasury, to the Speaker of the House of Representatives, to the Majority Leader of the Senate, to each Senator and Representative from California in the Congress of the United States, and to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
